sparkling and exotic ! unlike some of the other `` mondo '' albums , this collection may not be representative of the breadth and depth of indian music , but it makes for great listening all the same . `` mondo asian '' features primarily the polished , intricately textured compositions of r.a. rahman , billed as `` india 's greatest contemporary film composer '' . the cd cover continues : `` by incorporating western production styles and sensibilities to indian traditions , rahman has created a music that is universal even as it is distinctly indian . '' traditional indian instruments and vocal techniques merge with western harmonies and structures to create compositions that are as fascinating as they are fun . especially striking are the hypnotic track # 11 , `` gropika poornima '' , and track # 8 , the mysterious and sinuous `` suno re '' , which was written by rahman 's student , vishal